Icterus bullockii is a small bird belonging to the New World oriole family. 
It is about 22 cm in length and weighs around 35 grams. 
Its plumage is bright orange-yellow, with black wings, tail, and throat. 
The male has a black head and bib, while the female has a yellow-brown head. 
Icterus bullockii has a sharp and pointed bill, ideal for catching insects and nectar. 
This species is native to the western regions of North America, from Alaska to Central America. 
It is commonly found in riparian zones, wooded areas, and gardens.
